## Local enforcement hooks (the quality-gate harness)

CI blocks at the PR boundary; these hooks shift the same discipline **left**:

| Where | Mechanism | Blocks? |
|---|---|---|
| `git commit` | `.githooks/pre-commit` вЖТ `.claude/hooks/gate-runner.sh` runs `.dev/gates/*` on staged files | **yes** |
| `git push` | `.githooks/pre-push` runs `.dev/gates/push/*` | **yes** (`--no-verify` bypasses) |
| shared-tree stomp | `PreToolUse(Bash)` вЖТ `worktree-guard.sh` blocks `git checkout/switch/stash/reset --hard` when a live co-tenant shares the tree | **yes** (solo unaffected) |
| shared-tree edit | `PreToolUse(Edit)` вЖТ `worktree-guard-edit.sh` | warn (`WT_ENFORCE=block`) |
| commit fallback | `PreToolUse(Bash)` вЖТ `pretooluse-bash.sh` runs the gate when `core.hooksPath` isn't set | yes |

- **Per-clone setup:** `git config core.hooksPath .githooks`. The Claude hooks in
  `.claude/settings.json` + `.claude/hooks/` load automatically.
- **Worktree-per-session:** start Claude sessions with the `cw` shell function
  (wrapping `scripts/claude-worktree.sh`) so each session gets an isolated
  worktree вАФ auto-removed on exit if clean. Bypass a guard once with
  `WT_ALLOW_SHARED_TREE=1`.
- **Add gates** by dropping executable scripts in `.dev/gates/` (see its README).

